{"TopicId":87679,"ForumId":21,"TopicTitle":"North Pole Base Transport","CreatedByName":"Stewcumber","CreatedById":79928,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-10-17T19:35:11Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Stewcumber","CreatedById":79928,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-10-17T19:35:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EI haven\u0027t been on Kerbal or the forum for a while but suddenly got the urge to challenge myself to something. I decided to see if I could set up a base at the north pole, and then set a personal land speed record when I was there. Phase one was designing a plane to lug all my base stuff there.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EPelican I- A tristar rip off\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/13203382/OCUK/kerbal/Oct%2014/2014-10-10_00001%20%28Small%29.jpg\u0022 alt=\u00222014-10-10_00001%20%28Small%29.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EUnfortunately having a big lump of weight hanging underneath ruined the flight dynamics some what. So I tried to build the cargo into the design.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/13203382/OCUK/kerbal/Oct%2014/2014-10-10_00018%20%28Small%29.jpg\u0022 alt=\u00222014-10-10_00018%20%28Small%29.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/13203382/OCUK/kerbal/Oct%2014/2014-10-10_00057%20%28Small%29.jpg\u0022 alt=\u00222014-10-10_00057%20%28Small%29.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cem\u003Elong range but sub-sonic version, I just bolted extra fuel tanks to it; Jeb is ghetto like that.\u003C/em\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/13203382/OCUK/kerbal/Oct%2014/2014-10-10_00080%20%28Small%29.jpg\u0022 alt=\u00222014-10-10_00080%20%28Small%29.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/13203382/OCUK/kerbal/Oct%2014/2014-10-10_00055%20%28Small%29.jpg\u0022 alt=\u00222014-10-10_00055%20%28Small%29.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/13203382/OCUK/kerbal/Oct%2014/2014-10-11_00024%20%28Small%29.jpg\u0022 alt=\u00222014-10-11_00024%20%28Small%29.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cem\u003ESupersonic version with moaar engines!\u003C/em\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/13203382/OCUK/kerbal/Oct%2014/2014-10-11_00042%20%28Small%29.jpg\u0022 alt=\u00222014-10-11_00042%20%28Small%29.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cem\u003Esort of sucessful. Note lack of command module / cockpit on the base. Doh!\u003C/em\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/13203382/OCUK/kerbal/Oct%2014/2014-10-17_00001%20%28Small%29.jpg\u0022 alt=\u00222014-10-17_00001%20%28Small%29.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cem\u003Eadded a tail as the tail-less version was unflyable on the return journey\u003C/em\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cem\u003Efor some reason- it kept flipping over (due to the short length to width, \u003C/em\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cem\u003Epower and lift ratio, I guessed)\u003C/em\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/13203382/OCUK/kerbal/Oct%2014/2014-10-17_00005%20%28Small%29.jpg\u0022 alt=\u00222014-10-17_00005%20%28Small%29.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/13203382/OCUK/kerbal/Oct%2014/2014-10-17_00002%20%28Small%29.jpg\u0022 alt=\u00222014-10-17_00002%20%28Small%29.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/13203382/OCUK/kerbal/Oct%2014/2014-10-17_00008%20%28Small%29.jpg\u0022 alt=\u00222014-10-17_00008%20%28Small%29.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cem\u003EPelican VI and IV together\u003C/em\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/13203382/OCUK/kerbal/Oct%2014/2014-10-17_00014%20%28Small%29.jpg\u0022 alt=\u00222014-10-17_00014%20%28Small%29.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/13203382/OCUK/kerbal/Oct%2014/2014-10-17_00021%20%28Small%29.jpg\u0022 alt=\u00222014-10-17_00021%20%28Small%29.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cem\u003Enot exactly a big base but never mind!\u003C/em\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Redshift OTF","CreatedById":78679,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-10-18T14:31:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EYay, I love Polar bases. It\u0027s great to send planes there too. Loads of flat space to land on.\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}